sql:
SELECT feature_name, AVG(nbins) AS avg_nbins
FROM features
GROUP BY feature_name;

SELECT feature_name, nbins
FROM features
ORDER BY nbins DESC;

SELECT feature_name
FROM features
WHERE feature_id > 5;

external_knowledge:
- "stars of efficiency" are features with minimal time cost;
- "twinkled in the night sky" is used metaphorically to indicate those features that are active and have measurable time costs;
- "for less than a hundredth of a moment" refers to time costs less than 0.01, suggesting extremely high efficiency.

